2 Date: (Filing No. S- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 SENATE
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 623, L.D. 1539, “An Act to Create a
10 State Employee Compensation Stabilization Fund”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in paragraph A in the first line (page 1, line 4 in L.D.) by
12 striking out the following: "Eighty" and inserting the following: 'Eighty Seventy-five'
13 Amend the bill in section 2 in paragraph G in the first line (page 1, line 7 in L.D.) by
14 striking out the following: "Twenty Nineteen" and inserting the following: 'Twenty'
15 Amend the bill in section 3 in paragraph H in the first line (page 1, line 10 in L.D.) by
16 striking out the following: "One" and inserting the following: 'Five'
17 Amend the bill by inserting after section 4 the following:
18 'Sec. 5. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
19 allocations are made.
20 ADMINISTRATIVE AND FINANCIAL SERVICES, DEPARTMENT OF
21 State Employee Compensation Stabilization Fund N472
22 Initiative: Provides base allocations to authorize the expenditure of funds to pay for
23 stabilizing salaries of state employees.
24 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS 2025-26 2026-27
25 All Other $500 $500
26 __________ __________
27 OTHER SPECIAL REVENUE FUNDS TOTAL $500 $500
2284 '
29 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
30 number to read consecutively.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill by
3333 adjusting the percentage of the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund transferred to
Page 1 - 132LR1670(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 623, L.D. 1539
314 the State Employee Compensation Stabilization Fund at the close of the fiscal year from
325 1% to 5%. It also reduces the percentage transferred to the Maine Budget Stabilization
336 Fund under current law from 80% to 75% and amends the bill to remove the change in the
347 percentage transferred to the Highway and Bridge Capital program. The amendment adds
358 an appropriations and allocations section.
369 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
470 (See attached)
